This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it focuses on optimizing I/O workloads on computer clusters. Additionally, the use of distributed metadata management and system call interception techniques are commonly used in distributed computing. 

The Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category is also likely as the paper discusses the distribution of datasets to local storage, which involves managing and organizing data structures efficiently. 

The Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category is another possibility as the paper specifically targets Deep Learning applications and discusses the optimization of DL I/O. 

The Operating Systems (cs.OS) sub-category is also possible as the paper discusses the implementation of a runtime file system, which involves managing resources and scheduling tasks efficiently. 

Finally, the Scientific Computing (cs.SC) sub-category is a possibility as the paper discusses the optimization of DL training, which is a common task in scientific computing.
